race.comment: MIGHTY FEAT (5) was out of the money when resuming two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1000m at Albury, beaten 2.25 lengths into sixth. Has the talent to take care of this field. TURNAQUID (9) finished out of the money two starts back then she settled well back and was beaten 3 lengths when fourth over 1200m at Wagga a week ago. Finds a tougher race but a big run will not surprise. BOKEEM (4) is 6 from 34, which is a good strike-rate compared to most rivals here, and although now 8YO his recent trials suggest he's going well to figure here. KANIVA (11) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1115m at Kyneton, beaten 3 lengths into seventh after being prominent at the corner. No reason she can't bounce back here. SON OF ZORRO (7) has a moderate winning strike-rate but performed well last time at Wagga, finishing second and only a long neck from the winner at the end of 1000m.
